cpqRPMTrapDeviceConnected.name: cpqRPMTrapDeviceConnected
cpqRPMTrapDeviceConnected.description: A UPS device is reporting a Connection Lost due to one of the following. 1. The serial cable connected to the UPS has been unplugged. 2. The Network cable connected to the UPS has been unplugged. Recommendations: 1. Insure all cables are seated properly. 2. check you network to insure it is functioning properly. 3. If the UPS is serially connected insure that the Serial Relay Agent is installed and running.

If the UPS is serially connected insure that the Serial Relay Agent is installed and running.

cpqRPMTrapUPSInputVoltageAboveMax.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSInputVoltageAboveMax
cpqRPMTrapUPSInputVoltageAboveMax.description: A UPS device is reporting input voltage above maximum threshold.

cpqRPMTrapUPSInputVoltageNormal.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSInputVoltageNormal
cpqRPMTrapUPSInputVoltageNormal.description: A UPS device is reporting input voltage is out of range. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. 2. If the UPS remains on battery for an extended period of time it will not be able to sustain the load.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageBelowMin.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageBelowMin
cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageBelowMin.description: A UPS device is reporting output voltage below minimum threshold.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageAboveMax.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageAboveMax
cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageAboveMax.description: A UPS device is reporting output voltage above maximum threshold.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageNormal.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageNormal
cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputVoltageNormal.description: A UPS device is reporting output voltage is out of Range. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputOverload.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputOverload
cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputOverload.description: A UPS device is reporting an overload condition. Recommendations: 1. Reduce the load on the UPS by moving some of the load to another UPS. 2. Consider moving to a larger UPS to support the current load.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputOverloadCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputOverloadCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSOutputOverloadCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting an overload condition. Recommendations: 1. Reduce the load on the UPS by moving some of the load to another UPS. 2. Consider moving to a larger UPS to support the current load.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLow.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLow
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLow.description: A UPS device is reporting low battery. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. 2. When utility power is restored, charge the battery to it's full capacity. If the battery level continues to decrease, the UPS will not be able to sustain the output load!

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLowCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLowCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLowCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting low battery. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. 2. When utility power is restored, charge the battery to it's full capacity. If the battery level continues to decrease, the UPS will not be able to sustain the output load!

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDepleted.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDepleted
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDepleted.description: A UPS device is a depleted battery.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLevelNormal.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLevelNormal
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryLevelNormal.description: A UPS device is reporting low battery. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. 2. When utility power is restored, charge the battery to it's full capacity. If the battery level continues to decrease, the UPS will not be able to sustain the output load!

cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBattery.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBattery
cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBattery.description: A UPS device is reporting on battery condition. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. If the UPS remains on battery for an extended time it will not be able to sustain the output load!

cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBypass.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBypass
cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBypass.description: A UPS device is being bypassed.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBuck.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBuck
cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBuck.description: A UPS device is reporting an On Buck condition due to the following. 1. Utility power has increased above recommended utility input levels. Recommendation: 1. Contact an electrician.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBoost.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBoost
cpqRPMTrapUPSOnBoost.description: A UPS device is reporting an On Boost condition due to the following. 1. Utility power has dropped below recommended utility input levels. Recommendation: 1. Contact an electrician.

cpqRPMTrapUPSOnUtilityPower.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSOnUtilityPower
cpqRPMTrapUPSOnUtilityPower.description: A UPS device is reporting on battery condition. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. If the UPS remains on battery for an extended time it will not be able to sustain the output load!

cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureLow.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureLow
cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureLow.description: A UPS device is reporting temperature blow minimum threshold.

cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureHigh.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureHigh
cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureHigh.description: A UPS device is reporting temperature above maximum threshold.

cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureNormal.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureNormal
cpqRPMTrapUPSTemperatureNormal.description: A UPS device is reporting temperature is out of range. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is in a well ventilated area. 2. Lower the ambient temperature in the area where the UPS is located.

cpqRPMTrapUPSInternalFailure.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSInternalFailure
cpqRPMTrapUPSInternalFailure.description: A UPS device is reporting a general UPS failure. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSInternalFailureCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSInternalFailureCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSInternalFailureCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting a general UPS failure. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryFailure.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryFailure
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryFailure.description: A UPS device is reporting a battery failure. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support. 3. Your battery may need to be replaced. The UPS may not be capable of supporting it's load if utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryFailureCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryFailureCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryFailureCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting a battery failure. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support. 3. Your battery may need to be replaced. The UPS may not be capable of supporting it's load if utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSDiagnosticTestFailed.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSDiagnosticTestFailed
cpqRPMTrapUPSDiagnosticTestFailed.description: A UPS device is reporting a diagnostic test failed. Recommendations: 1. Your battery may need to be replaced. 2. If this error persists contact technical support. 3. The UPS may not be capable of supporting it's load if utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSDiagnosticTestSucceeded.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSDiagnosticTestSucceeded
cpqRPMTrapUPSDiagnosticTestSucceeded.description: A UPS device is reporting a diagnostic test failed. Recommendations: 1. Your battery may need to be replaced. 2. If this error persists contact technical support. 3. The UPS may not be capable of supporting it's load if utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSInputUnderOverFreq.description: Input (Utility) fault: measured input frequency is outside of either the upper or lower frequency limit specification for normal operation.

cpqRPMTrapUPSDCStartOccurred.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSDCStartOccurred
cpqRPMTrapUPSDCStartOccurred.description: The UPS has been started on battery when AC input power is not present. This alarm is used to record the date and time of this event.

cpqRPMTrapUPSDCStartOccurredCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSDCStartOccurredCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSDCStartOccurredCleared.description: The UPS has been started on utility while AC input power is present.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassNotAvailable.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassNotAvailable
cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassNotAvailable.description: A UPS device is reporting bypass not avaliable. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassNotAvailableCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassNotAvailableCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassNotAvailableCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting bypass not avaliable. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityFail.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityFail
cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityFail.description: Indicates that the utility input power is not within predetermined limits. This could be, but is not limited to, over voltage, under voltage, over frequency, under frequency or over current.

cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityFailCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityFailCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityFailCleared.description: Indicates that the utility input power is within predetermined limits.

cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityNotPresent.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityNotPresent
cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityNotPresent.description: Indicates that the utility input is not present. This differs from alarm #57 in that the detected voltage is zero in this case.

cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityNotPresentCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityNotPresentCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSUtilityNotPresentCleared.description: Indicates that the utility input is present.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassManualTurnedOn.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassManualTurnedOn
cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassManualTurnedOn.description: The bypass has been given a manual turn on command.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassManualTurnedOff.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassManualTurnedOff
cpqRPMTrapUPSBypassManualTurnedOff.description: The bypass has been given a manual turn off command.

cpqRPMTrapUPSSiteWiringFault.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSSiteWiringFault
cpqRPMTrapUPSSiteWiringFault.description: A UPS device is reporting a fault in the input wiring, other than Phase Rotation: e.g., Ground/Neutral reversed. Recommendations: 1. Contact an electrician.

cpqRPMTrapUPSSiteWiringNormal.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSSiteWiringNormal
cpqRPMTrapUPSSiteWiringNormal.description: A UPS device is reporting a fault in the input wiring, other than Phase Rotation: e.g., Ground/Neutral reversed. Recommendations: 1. Contact an electrician.

cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOffManual.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOffManual
cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOffManual.description: A UPS device is operating in manual bypass mode. Recommendations: 1. In bypass mode, the UPS cannot support devices if there is a power failure. 2. Once maintenance has been performed return the UPS to normal mode.

cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassONManual.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassONManual
cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassONManual.description: A UPS device is operating in manual bypass mode. Recommendations: 1. In bypass mode, the UPS cannot support devices if there is a power failure. 2. Once maintenance has been performed return the UPS to normal mode.

cppqRPMtrapUPSStartedOnBatteryCleared.name: cppqRPMtrapUPSStartedOnBatteryCleared
cppqRPMtrapUPSStartedOnBatteryCleared.description: A UPS device has been started while on battery power. AC input power is not present. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. If the UPS remains on battery for an extended time it will not be able to sustain the output load!

cppqRPMtrapUPSStartedOnBattery.name: cppqRPMtrapUPSStartedOnBattery
cppqRPMtrapUPSStartedOnBattery.description: A UPS device has been started while on battery power. AC input power is not present. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. If the UPS remains on battery for an extended time it will not be able to sustain the output load.

cpqRPMtrapUPSInputOutofRangeCleared.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSInputOutofRangeCleared
cpqRPMtrapUPSInputOutofRangeCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting input voltage is out of range. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. 2. If the UPS remains on battery for an extended period of time it will not be able to sustain the load.

cpqRPMtrapUPSInputOutofRange.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSInputOutofRange
cpqRPMtrapUPSInputOutofRange.description: A UPS device is reporting input voltage is out of range. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is plugged into an outlet supplied with utility power. 2. If the UPS remains on battery for an extended period of time it will not be able to sustain the load.

cpqRPMtrapUPSTemperatureOutOfRange.description: A UPS device is reporting temperature is out of range. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is in a well ventilated area. 2. Lower the ambient temperature in the area where the UPS is located.

cpqRPMtrapUPSTemperatureOutOfRangeCleare.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSTemperatureOutOfRangeCleared
cpqRPMtrapUPSTemperatureOutOfRangeCleare.description: A UPS device is reporting temperature is out of range. Recommendations: 1. Check to make sure the UPS is in a well ventilated area. 2. Lower the ambient temperature in the area where the UPS is located.

cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOnAuto.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOnAuto
cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOnAuto.description: A UPS device is operating in auto bypass mode. Recommendations: 1. In bypass mode, the UPS cannot support devices if there is a power failure. 2. Once maintenance has been performed return the UPS to normal mode.

cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOnAutoCleared.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOnAutoCleared
cpqRPMtrapUPSBypassOnAutoCleared.description: A UPS device is operating in auto bypass mode. Recommendations: 1. In bypass mode, the UPS cannot support devices if there is a power failure. 2. Once maintenance has been performed return the UPS to normal mode.

cpqRPMtrapUPSOutputoutofRange.name: cpqRPMtrapUPSOutputoutofRange
cpqRPMtrapUPSOutputoutofRange.description: A UPS device is reporting output voltage is out of Range. Recommendations: 1. Initiate a UPS self test. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteriesDisconnected.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteriesDisconnected
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteriesDisconnected.description: A UPS device is reporting batteries are not connected to the UPS. Recomendations: 1. Connect the UPS Batteries. The UPS will not be capable of supporting it's load if the utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteriesDisconnectedCleare.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteriesDisconnectedCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteriesDisconnectedCleare.description: A UPS device is reporting batteries are not connected to the UPS. Recomendations: 1. Connect the UPS Batteries. The UPS will not be capable of supporting it's load if the utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDischarged.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDischarged
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDischarged.description: A UPS device is reporting batteries are completely discharged. Recommendations: 1. Connect the UPS to utility power to charge the batteries. The UPS will not be able to support it's load if the utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDischargedCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDischargedCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSBatteryDischargedCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting batteries are completely discharged. Recommendations: 1. Connect the UPS to utility power to charge the batteries. The UPS will not be able to support it's load if the utility power fails!

cpqRPMTrapUPSCheckBreaker.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSCheckBreaker
cpqRPMTrapUPSCheckBreaker.description: A UPS device is reporting an output Breaker or Relay has failed or may be stuck open or closed with this alarm. Recommendations: 1. Check all breakers on the UPS. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSCheckBreakerCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSCheckBreakerCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSCheckBreakerCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting an output Breaker or Relay has failed or may be stuck open or closed with this alarm. Recommendations: 1. Check all breakers on the UPS. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSEPOInitiated.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSEPOInitiated
cpqRPMTrapUPSEPOInitiated.description: A UPS device is reporting an Emergency Power Off (EPO) command has been received to shutdown the UPS immediately with out delay. This command may come from a local control panel or from a remote source. Recommendations: 1. Turn the UPS on to reapply power to attached equipment.

cpqRPMTrapUPSManualLoadDumped.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSManualLoadDumped
cpqRPMTrapUPSManualLoadDumped.description: The UPS has been powered off with user interaction.

cpqRPMTrapUPSManualLoadDumpedCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSManualLoadDumpedCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSManualLoadDumpedCleared.description: The UPS has been powered off with user interaction.

cpqRPMTrapUPSCabinetDoorOpen.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSCabinetDoorOpen
cpqRPMTrapUPSCabinetDoorOpen.description: A UPS device is reporting a cover panel has been removed while utility power is present. Recommendations: 1. Reinstall all panels. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSCabinetDoorOpenCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSCabinetDoorOpenCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSCabinetDoorOpenCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting a cover panel has been removed while utility power is present. Recommendations: 1. Reinstall all panels. 2. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSFanFailure.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSFanFailure
cpqRPMTrapUPSFanFailure.description: A UPS device is reporting a fan failure has occurred. Recommendations: 1. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSFanFailureCleared.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSFanFailureCleared
cpqRPMTrapUPSFanFailureCleared.description: A UPS device is reporting a fan failure has occurred. Recommendations: 1. If this error persists contact technical support.

cpqRPMTrapUPSLossOfRedundancy.name: cpqRPMTrapUPSLossOfRedundancy
cpqRPMTrapUPSLossOfRedundancy.description: A UPS device is reporting a loss of redundancy due to one of the following. 1. One or more of the Electronics Modules has failed 2. One or more of the electronics modules has been manually removed. 3. The amount of load on the UPS has increased to the point that the UPS is no longer able to support an N+1 configuration. Recommendations: 1. Check the UPS to see if one of the modules has failed. 2. Make sure that all modules are securely plugged in. 3. Reduce the load to return the N+1 configuration. 4. If the amount of load is now going to exceed and N+1 configuration permanently, change the configuration on the front panel of the UPS to Capacity instead of Parallel N+1.
